Class Weighted<T>

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.susx.mlcl.byblo.io.Weighted<T>
Type Parameters:
T - Type of record being weighted
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<Weighted<T>>
public class Weighted<T>
extends Object
implements Serializable, Comparable<Weighted<T>>

Weighted objects represent a weighting or frequency applied to some discrete record.

Instances of Weighted are immutable.

Author:
Hamish I A Morgan <hamish.morgan@sussex.ac.uk>

equals

public boolean equals(Object obj)
Indicates whether some other object is "equal to" this one.

Note that only the entryId field is used for equality. I.e two objects with the same entryId, but differing weights will be consider equal.
